        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Oct 14 1852</date></p>
            <p>Rev. <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear &#38; Rev Sir&#44;&#8211;</p>
            <p><add>Hebrew</add>. You will therefore excuse<lb/> me when I write you in the most
                laconic manner<lb/> Our <add>Hebrew</add> in Greene St. have established a
                school<lb/> which we intend to open the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Sunday in Dec.<lb/>
                I am one of Directors and I shall recommend.<lb/> them to purchase a large quantity
                of your <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> I would therefore wish you to let me know<lb/> at
                what price you would sell us 50 or 100<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
                <hi rend="underline">unbound</hi> for each also your <add>Hebrew</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will please copy three advertisements<lb/> from the Asmonean of tomorrow and
                change</p>
        </body>
    </text>
